fying building staff in the case of emergency, and generally providing customer service. Part-time Desk Clerks are expected to learn Housing policies and be able to explain and enforce those policies. This position is under the supervision of the Day Desk Clerk and the Hall Director. Minimum Qualifications Ability to communicate clearly and effectively, demonstrating  excellent use of the English language Punctuality and dependability Ability to work without close supervision Ability to work well with others Work Schedule Part-time Desk Clerk shifts available vary by hall. Most desk shifts available are during evenings and weekends, including overnight on weekends. Application Process Part-time Desk Clerks are hired at the beginning of each semester and at the end of spring for summer work. Students interested in a Part-time Desk Clerk position should apply online through the Career Center at http://careercenter.unt.edu and follow any additional instructions included in the job posting. The Part-time Desk Clerk position is posted only for students who have accepted College Work Study through Financial Aid. Visit Us Crumley Hall UNT Housing 1621 W. Highland St. Denton, TX 76201 Mail Us UNT Housing 1155 Union Circle #311310 Denton, TX 76203 Phone: (940) 565-2610 Fax: (940) 369-8764 Contact Us (940) 565-2610 housinginfo@unt.edu Technical issues? Site last updated on May 09, 2017 Disclaimer| AA/EOE/ADA| Privacy| Electronic Accessibility| State of Texas Online| Emergency Preparedness| THECB Online Resume System Student Consumer Information| UNT Compliance Hotline| Governors Committee on People with Disabilities| Texas Veterans Portal| UNT Home Site last updated on May 09, 2017 | Important Links 